      <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-a" id="what-is-the-best-length-for-a-quora-answer"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>The Semrush study of 26,000 cited Quora URLs found that cited answers averaged 535+ words. We recommend 400 to 800 words as the optimal range. Shorter than 400 words rarely provides enough depth for AI extraction. Longer than 800 words risks losing reader attention unless the content is exceptionally information-dense. The first paragraph matters most. Make it a direct, complete answer in 15 to 30 words.</p></div></div>
